Dodo!

15:29.471 --> 15:30.736
Dodo!

15:31.606 --> 15:33.972
Dodo!

15:39.615 --> 15:43.783
Dodo!
Aah!

15:43.785 --> 15:46.119
So you want to get famous?

15:46.121 --> 15:47.486
Yes.

15:47.488 --> 15:48.821
I think you need
to do something

15:48.823 --> 15:49.822
that makes a splash.

15:49.824 --> 15:52.124
I like where you're going
with this.

15:52.126 --> 15:54.126
You're going to be
the first people

15:54.128 --> 15:57.029
to go over Niagara Falls
in a barrel!

15:57.031 --> 15:59.432
Aah!

15:59.434 --> 16:02.501
You'll be the famous
Bellacourt Barrel Sisters,

16:02.503 --> 16:07.542
and all you have to do
is go down the falls like this.

16:09.977 --> 16:11.778
Well, you get the idea.

16:11.780 --> 16:16.081
Commodore has tasked me with
finding Lillian and Beatrice.

16:16.083 --> 16:18.585
<i>And if there is a Bellacourt
within a thousand miles of me,</i>

16:18.587 --> 16:20.352
<i>then by God,
like pieces of lint</i>

16:20.354 --> 16:22.322
<i>on a freshly pressed
cummerbund,</i>

16:22.324 --> 16:24.523
<i>I'll sniff them out.</i>

16:24.525 --> 16:26.893
<i>Not until I found that
god-awful Pee-nuh-lope woman</i>

16:26.895 --> 16:29.394
<i>in all of her middle-class
squalor did I discover</i>

16:29.396 --> 16:32.365
<i>all this waterfall nonsense.</i>

16:36.871 --> 16:38.437
Oh, no!

16:41.944 --> 16:43.842
Oh, no!

16:43.844 --> 16:45.278
Where are they?

16:45.280 --> 16:46.479
I don't know.

16:46.481 --> 16:47.547
No!
Not the baby!

16:47.549 --> 16:49.316
Where are they?

16:49.318 --> 16:52.719
Okay, I'll tell you!

16:52.721 --> 16:54.488
You were about to tell me,

16:54.490 --> 16:56.222
and I threw the baby.

16:56.224 --> 16:57.891
I did not expect you
to tell me.

16:57.893 --> 16:59.092
That's why I threw the baby.

16:59.094 --> 17:00.026
I am so sorry.
I am so very sorry.

17:00.028 --> 17:02.461
He's not crying!

17:02.463 --> 17:04.230
I'm sure he's fine.
I'll go get the baby.

17:04.232 --> 17:06.232
No!

17:06.233 --> 17:09.300
There he is.
I think he's fine.

17:09.303 --> 17:11.002
I think he's fine.

17:11.005 --> 17:11.671
- Oh!
- No worse for the wear.

17:11.673 --> 17:13.172
What's wrong with you?

17:13.174 --> 17:15.008
I lost my temper
and I apologize.

17:20.580 --> 17:23.415
Are you sure this
is a good idea?

17:23.417 --> 17:25.416
Beatrice, I've never
seen anyone be such a baby

17:25.419 --> 17:28.252
about going over a
160-foot waterfall in a barrel.

17:28.255 --> 17:30.189
Oh.

17:30.191 --> 17:31.223
How do we look?

17:31.225 --> 17:32.592
Like two white women.

17:32.594 --> 17:34.093
Now get down in the barrel.

17:34.095 --> 17:35.627
Get in there.
Get in there.

17:35.629 --> 17:37.431
Get on.

17:40.268 --> 17:42.734
Oh! Can I have my lucky ship
in a bottle?

17:42.736 --> 17:44.269
As you wish.

17:44.271 --> 17:46.373
- There you go.
- Thank you!

17:46.375 --> 17:48.042
Now get down in there
really good.

17:52.312 --> 17:55.082
They'll be dead on impact.

17:56.451 --> 17:58.116
Wait.
What did he say?

17:58.118 --> 17:59.885
I heard, "Good luck!"

18:10.197 --> 18:12.265
Ooh!

18:13.868 --> 18:17.737
I just want you to know...

18:17.739 --> 18:19.071
if anything happens to us,
I really,

18:19.073 --> 18:22.407
really loved being rich.

18:29.082 --> 18:31.886
Nooooo!

18:34.188 --> 18:35.156
My God!

18:35.158 --> 18:36.622
He's magnificent.

18:36.624 --> 18:40.761
I shall name you Kermit.
Kermit the Baby.

18:40.763 --> 18:43.863
Yes.
"Kermit. Kermit the Baby."

18:43.865 --> 18:46.568
The repetition will help people
remember his name.

18:52.675 --> 18:55.076
Oh, God!
Girls!

18:55.078 --> 18:57.110
Oh! Oh-ho-ho-ho!

18:57.112 --> 18:59.580
Oh, girls!
Oh! Oh! Oh!

18:59.582 --> 19:00.680
Lady Beatrice!
Lady Beatrice!

19:00.682 --> 19:03.283
- Ah!
- Oh! Oh, you're all right!

19:03.285 --> 19:05.285
Oh! Oh-ho-ho-ho-ho!

19:05.287 --> 19:06.753
Stand up.
Stand up, Lady Beatrice!

19:06.755 --> 19:08.355
There you are!
There you are!

19:08.357 --> 19:10.523
Lillian!
Lady Lillian!

19:10.525 --> 19:11.491
Oh-ho-ho-ho-ho!

19:11.493 --> 19:14.762
You're alive!
Upsy-daisy.

19:14.764 --> 19:16.597
There you are, dear.
Stand up.

19:16.599 --> 19:17.965
There you are.

19:17.967 --> 19:22.334
Ladies and gentlemen,
Harriet Tubman!

19:22.336 --> 19:24.571
Thank you, all.

19:24.573 --> 19:27.808
- Harriet, we did it!
- We're alive!

19:27.810 --> 19:29.944
So it brings me great pleasure
to introduce my newest venture.

19:29.946 --> 19:30.778
Harriet?

19:30.780 --> 19:32.812
Tubman's Man-Tubs.

19:32.814 --> 19:34.549
"The Strongest Tub
a Man Can Buy."

19:34.551 --> 19:37.451
Even those two
pathetic heiresses

19:37.453 --> 19:40.154
survived a tumble in my tub!

19:42.291 --> 19:44.558
- What?
- Uh, no! No!

19:44.560 --> 19:46.292
She's taking all the attention!

19:46.294 --> 19:49.128
She Jelson Paramour'd us!

19:49.130 --> 19:50.296
Shh.

19:50.298 --> 19:51.965
Come on, girls.

19:51.967 --> 19:53.266
Let's go home.

19:53.268 --> 19:58.304
♪ Let's go home ♪

19:58.306 --> 20:01.007
♪ Let's go home ♪

20:04.647 --> 20:06.346
Daddy, I'm so happy
we're home.

20:06.348 --> 20:08.648
Yes, could one of your lawyers
draw us a Beluga bath?

20:08.650 --> 20:10.850
Not so fast.

20:10.852 --> 20:12.785
Here's how this
is going to work.

20:12.787 --> 20:15.321
I will allow you to return
to Bellacourt Manor

20:15.323 --> 20:19.392
under one condition.

20:19.394 --> 20:21.695
I've had my legal team
draw up documents.

20:21.697 --> 20:24.831
You will sign them, annulling
your respective marriages

20:24.833 --> 20:26.332
to Victor and Albert.

20:26.334 --> 20:28.468
I know you love your husbands.

20:28.470 --> 20:30.036
You've spent
your lives together.

20:30.038 --> 20:32.673
- This must be difficult for you.
- Mm-mm.

20:32.675 --> 20:34.876
But in order
to save this family,

20:34.878 --> 20:41.715
I need you to start dating rich,
eligible bachelors.

20:41.717 --> 20:43.686
Do you understand?

20:47.622 --> 20:50.124
Oh, that's a daddy's girls!

20:50.126 --> 20:52.693
Ooh!

20:52.695 --> 20:54.026
Ah, ah, ah, not that one.
Thank you.

